member.name: F:GSR.EnDecic.CoderSettings.SIGNIFICANT_ONLY
member.summary:
Only encode or expect significant data. Leaving off any inferrable data.
For example the keys in a map, when the map will always have certain keys that only help with human readability

member.name: F:GSR.EnDecic.CoderSettings.NO_OPTIONALS
member.summary:
Encode or expect no optional data to be present.
NOTE: optional data is not the same as insignificant data.

member.name: F:GSR.EnDecic.CoderSettings.ALL_OPTIONALS
member.summary:
Encode or expect all optional data to be present.
NOTE: optional data is not the same as insignificant data.

member.name: F:GSR.EnDecic.CoderSettings.MAXIMAL_EXTRACTION
member.summary: Decode or apply as much data as is possible. If a field can't be decoded, skip it and proceed before throwing exception.

member.name: F:GSR.EnDecic.CoderSettings.TOLERANT
member.summary:
Tolerate data to the format when a unique representation can be found.
For instance using the Json encoding of a non string object as a key in a Json object.

member.name: F:GSR.EnDecic.CoderSettings.DEFAULT
member.summary: All options disabled.
